SIMPLE: fiddlehead
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fiddlehead
<hw>fid"dle*head`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>any of several
tall ferns of northern temperate regions having graceful arched fronds
and sporophylls resembling ostrich plumes.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ostrich fern, shuttlecock fern, <spn>Matteuccia
struthiopteris</spn>, <spn>Pteretis struthiopteris</spn>, <spn>Onoclea
struthiopteris</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>New World fern (<spn>Osmunda cinnamonea</spn>)
having woolly cinnamon-colored spore-bearing fronds in early spring
later surrounded by green fronds, called also <altname>fiddlehead
fern</altname>; the early uncurling fronds are edible, and sometimes
considered as a vegetable delicacy.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cinnamon fern, fiddlehead fern, <spn>Osmunda
cinnamonea</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>an ornament on a ship's bow,
curved like the volute or scroll at the head of a violin. Sometimes it
serves the function of a <er>billhead</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fiddleneck</ent>⟦br⟧
